text: Juhani Keto (20 September 1947 – 26 August 2018) was a Finnish basketball player. Keto was a six-time Finnish champion and three-time Finnish Cup winner. Representing Tapion Honka, Turun NMKY and Torpan Pojat, he also achieved two SM-sarja bronze medals.Juhani Keto – Finnish Basketball Association Keto had 74 caps for the Finnish national team with whom he won Nordic championship in 1968 and took part in 1972 Olympic Trials.National Team Statistics – Finnish Basketball Association Keto died at the age of 70 on August 26, 2018. His daughter was one time married to world record swimmer Jani Sievinen. ==Trophies and awards== * SM-sarja championship in 1969, 1970, 1971, 1972, 1973, and 1978 ** bronze in 1974 and 1977 * Finnish cup championship in 1968, 1971, and 1972 * Nordic championship with national team in 1968 ==Sources== * * ==References== Category:1947 births Category:2018 deaths Category:Finnish men's basketball players Category:Sportspeople from Helsinki Category:Torpan Pojat players Category:Centers (basketball) Category:Power forwards (basketball)
